## table card | under=proj_default | doc="Task-relations demo. Four tasks demonstrate the parent_task/parent_relationship pair: 'Auth rewrite' is a standalone head task; the next three reference it via parent_task with three different relationship tags (subtask / blocker / related). The 'Head tasks' filter on the grid uses (parent_task not exists OR parent_task has_phase terminal) so these children stay hidden until their parent reaches Done/Cancelled — that's the canonical 'current head tasks only' view."
### rows
card_type_id,    parent_card_id, title,                        status,   assignee,             parent_task,      parent_relationship, sort_order, alias
$card_type.task, parent,         "Auth rewrite",               @s_doing, $user_account.alice,  null,             null,                50,         t_auth_root
$card_type.task, parent,         "Migrate session storage",    @s_todo,  $user_account.bob,    @t_auth_root,     subtask,             60,         t_auth_session
$card_type.task, parent,         "JWKS validation blocker",    @s_doing, $user_account.dave,   @t_auth_root,     blocker,             70,         t_auth_jwks
$card_type.task, parent,         "Audit-log review (related)", @s_review,$user_account.carol,  @t_auth_root,     related,             80,         t_auth_audit


-- Screens + their default filters. The screen→default_filter wiring
-- is a circular reference (screen needs filter.id; filter needs
-- screen.id as parent). The loader's toposort can't break that;
-- the original PL/pgSQL inserted screen, then filter, then a
-- separate UPDATE to set default_filter. For Phase 2 we omit the
-- default_filter attribute on demo screens — the runtime
-- screen.runInsert hook handles this for newly-created projects;
-- tests don't cover demo-screen default_filter wiring.

## table card | under=proj_default | doc="Inbox screen. flow_ref binds the screen to the project's task flow so the TransitionBar in the task-detail header surfaces labelled transitions (Accept / Start / Send to review / Approve / Cancel / Reopen). Without flow_ref the bar renders empty."
### rows
card_type_id, parent_card_id, title,   layout, slug,  hotkey, sort_order, flow_ref,       alias, toggle_groups
