## table card | under=proj_default | doc="Named-filter snippets — reusable predicate chunks the user pulls into any screen's active filter via the 'Named' multi-select. The two date snippets reference the relative-date ops (before_today / within_days), which the server compiler resolves against now()::date at query time so the result keeps moving with the clock instead of going stale on save. The non-terminal status check uses has_phase [triage, active] (the kernel form) so the advanced filter editor renders the op label cleanly. 'Heads' surfaces top-level tasks (no parent OR parent terminal)."
### rows
card_type_id,               parent_card_id, title,                    predicate
$card_type.predicate_snippet, parent,         "Overdue",                `{"connective":"and","children":[{"attr":"status","op":"has_phase","values":["triage","active"]},{"attr":"due_date","op":"before_today"}]}`
$card_type.predicate_snippet, parent,         "Due within 3 days",      `{"connective":"and","children":[{"attr":"status","op":"has_phase","values":["triage","active"]},{"attr":"due_date","op":"within_days","values":[3]}]}`
$card_type.predicate_snippet, parent,         "Heads",                  `{"connective":"or","children":[{"attr":"parent_task","op":"not exists"},{"attr":"parent_task","op":"has_phase","values":["terminal"]}]}`


-- ---------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Second demo project: "Mobile App"
--
-- A lighter second project so the project picker, cross-project task
-- moves, the named-filter admin, and the global "All projects" inbox
-- all have something to chew on in dev. Keeps the demo footprint
-- modest (8 tasks vs Default Project's 29) — the goal is variety, not
-- density. Every alias uses a `mob_` prefix to stay out of
-- Default Project's `s_*` / `m_*` / `c_*` / `t_*` / `sc_*` namespace.
-- ---------------------------------------------------------------------

